description:
**Please use the Wrights Road entrance to the stadium car park. You will be directed where to go upon entry.**
**This is a busy site, please allow at least 1 hour for the entire process. Bring a book, your knitting and/or your phone charger to occupy yourself in the queue**


*Please note this is a drive in clinic. For your and our safety, pedestrians will not be permitted.*


People being vaccinated must be seated next to a window and their full arm/shoulder must be accessible through the window.
You’ll be asked to queue. You’ll need to park and wait for twenty minutes following your vaccination. 

**You are welcome to bring along any friends and whānau to be vaccinated, you do not need to have a booking to be vaccinated at this site.**

description:
We have returned to the pharmacy after running a successful vaccination centre at Riverstone Recreation Hall at Whirinaki. If alert levels or demand change we may return to the Hall. Keep an eye on our facebook page for updates: 
https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100054237188521 
 
You will need to wait and be observed for 15 minutes after your vaccination.
 
You must wear a facemask and be prepared to expose your full shoulder and upper arm without removing the facemask.
 
DO NOT ATTEND – PLEASE REBOOK If you are unwell with cold or flu like symptoms, sore throat, cough a high fever etc, have been to any locations of interest, are awaiting a COVID test or have been asked to stay home and self isolate.
